<br>
1) Make sure to hit every mob at least once, especially ones that don't appear to be attacking anyone.  This will make sure that all the mobs know you're there.  NPCs always attack the warrior first as long as you've made them aware of your presence.<br>
<br>
2) Always use aggressive on tough pulls, due to the amazing damage you do with this discipline you gain a psychological advantage over the mob you're tanking, hence reducing their damage output.<br>
<br>
3) Never assist anyone on raids.  You are a warrior, everyone should be assisting you, even the MA.  The sooner you can slip into this mentality the sooner your raids will start owning.<br>
<br>
4) Use your best taunting weaps at all times.  This will ensure that should the MT die, you will be guaranteed aggro.  In fact using this technique will usually get you aggro before anyone else, which is very important as a warrior.<br>
<br>
5) Always scout ahead.  As a warrior it's your job to know exactly what the pull team is doing, make sure you're right up there with them running ahead.  A good warrior won't even need the monk to tell them went to tag, as long as there is 10 mobs or less, go ahead and pull them.<br>
<br>
6) If the clerics are even a 1/2 second too slow healing you, be sure to tell them to goto hell because they are n00bs and don't know how to play their class.  Make sure you do this in all caps.  This will tell the clerics that they need to play better and after just a few uses you will notice a drastic change in cleric behavior.  In fact, make a hotkey for this.<br>
<br>
<br>
These 6 easy rules are the key to making successful raids.  Any warrior that follows these rules to the letter will notice amazing changes to both the raid and everyone's attitudes towards them.<br>
<br>
