<br>
However, i'd like to take the time to Define some of the terms used as he sorta assumes everyone knows what these terms mean (basically, dumbing it up even more...heh)<br>
<br>
Main Assist - This is the central player character that the healing is going to be focused on. Players not doing the Main Assist (or MA) role, are required to position themselves behind the mob to avoid unneeded damage. Every raider should have a hotkey made with /assist &lt;name of MA&gt;.<br>
<br>
Secondary Assist - Same role as MA, but is second in line for duties. Provided the untimely death of the MA, the SA will step up and act as MA until the original MA is back on his feet.<br>
<br>
Tank Mezzing - The process of using a melee (tank) class to engage a mob alone with healing back up that enchanters are unable to mesmerise using thier lines of spells. This pre-occupies the mob from the rest of the raid battle much like the enchanter/bard spell/song would do. This is usually done on creatures in a room where the primary target is. These creatures are usually referred to as guards or pets.<br>
<br>
Pre-Taunt - This is when the MA is given a &quot;head start&quot; of gaining initial aggro. The rest of the raiding crew stands out of harms way for a certain period of time, while the MA attacks the creature alone, generating hate. <br>
<br>
Tank Order/Switching - A technique used by designating certain melee types (mainly warriors) to form a chain of tanking. Using the /discipline defensive, the warriors will take turns being MA. once /disc defensive is almost over, the next tank in the line will take over as MA.<br>
<br>
<br>
Some important tid bits worth mentioning :<br>
